<section class="expert-philosophy">
    <h2>Core Philosophy & Approach</h2>

    <blockquote class="featured-quote">
        "The coronary calcium score is the single strongest predictor of cardiac events we have - better than any blood test, better than any traditional risk factor. A CAC of zero is incredibly reassuring, and a high CAC tells you disease is present regardless of what other tests show."
    </blockquote>

    <p>Dr. Matthew Budoff has dedicated his career to validating and advancing coronary artery calcium (CAC) scoring as a tool for cardiovascular risk assessment. His research has been instrumental in establishing CAC as one of the most powerful predictors of heart attack risk available.</p>

    <p>He has been a key investigator in major studies, including MESA (Multi-Ethnic Study of Atherosclerosis), that have demonstrated the predictive power of CAC scoring across different populations.</p>

    <div class="key-point">
        <h3>Central Arguments</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>CAC is highly predictive</strong> - Coronary calcium scoring predicts cardiovascular events better than traditional risk factors</li>
            <li><strong>Zero score is powerful</strong> - A CAC of zero indicates very low short-term risk, even with other risk factors</li>
            <li><strong>Direct disease detection</strong> - CAC directly measures atherosclerosis, unlike blood tests which measure risk markers</li>
            <li><strong>Risk stratification</strong> - CAC can reclassify risk for patients in intermediate-risk categories</li>
            <li><strong>Treatment decisions</strong> - CAC results can guide decisions about preventive therapies like statins</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

